In Acumatica ERP Construction                         Edition, you can configure a project with contract cap retainage to be able to define the maximum retainage amount that can be held per project. For a project with the contract cap retainage, you perform progress billing, and the particular invoice amount is retained until the specified retainage limit is reached. {br}{TOC}
==Learning Objectives==
In this chapter, you will do the following:[anchor|#_13a85a70-12c8-493c-a309-eaf5a2d06d14]
*Learn how to configure a project with contract cap and which settings affect the calculation
*Learn how the contract cap retainage is calculated
*Create pro forma invoices with retainage for the project until retainage cap is reached
*Release retainage for the project by several project budget lines

==Applicable Scenarios==
You configure a project with contract cap retainage when it is necessary to set the maximum retainage amount that can be held per project. When billing a project with contract cap retainage, the retainage is withheld for the invoice lines until the specified contract cap is reached.[anchor|#section_it2_vcv_qmb]
==Rules to Apply Retainage with Contract Cap==
Construction projects are typically billed by progress: it is assumed that the customer have to make partial payments to the general contractor as the work progresses. Requests for payments are prepared periodically, for example, monthly, and include the cost of the work accomplished since the previous payment to the general contractor has been made.{br}

In accordance with the project terms, the customer usually retains a prescribed percentage of each progress payment being made; a typical scenario is billing a project with a contract cap retainage, which means that the retainage is being withheld until it reaches agreed amount (which is typically specified as the percentage of the total project amount). After that, is the work is progressing satisfyingly, the subsequent progress payments are performed in full. The accumulated retainage is being held by the customer until the work receives final certification by the architect. Once the customer accepts the project, the final payment that includes the accumulated retainage is made to the general contractor.
When you bill a project for which the retainage with contract cap is configured, the selected contract cap retainage is applied to a project when you bill a project until the cap is reached. {br}

After the cap has been reached and the '''Total Retained Amount''' held per project is at its maximum, no new retainage amount is calculated for further invoices created during project billing. The '''Total Retained Amount''' held per project is reallocated between the invoice lines based on their weight and retainage capacity. That is, the invoices have the same total '''Allocated Retained Amount''' but with different portions of it in the invoice lines (which allocated to the lines is based on calculated line weight).{br}

You can gradually release the retainage held on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_51_00_00|Release AR Retainage] ([~/?ScreenId=AR510000|AR510000]) form to clear the '''Unreleased Retainage''' balance held on the AR invoice lines; this in turn cause decreasing of the '''Retained Amount'''in revenue budget lines on the '''Revenue Budget''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form. {br}

The total retainage amount held per project ('''Total Retained Amount''') stays the same across all the invoices prepared for the projectunless a change order that affects the project revenue budget has been released. If you configure the project to include change orders in the retainage calculation (that is, the '''Include CO''' check box is selected on the '''Summary''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] ([~/?ScreenId=PM301000|PM301000]) form), the contract total, completed percentage and the cap amount are recalculated in accordance with the changes in the revenue budget that has been introduced by the released change orders.[anchor|#section_tsd_ydv_qmb]
==Calculation of Retainage Amounts==
In a pro forma invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_70_00|Pro Forma Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=PM307000|PM307000]) form prepared for a project with contract cap retainage, the system calculates the '''Allocated Retained Amount''' (that is, the amount of retainage that is considered to be held for the related revenue budget line in this pro forma invoice), by using the following formula:{br}

{{Allocated Retained Amount = (Total Retained Amount - Total Released Retainage) * Line Weight}}{br}

In this formula:{br}

{{Total Retained Amount}} is the sum of retained amounts summed up by all revenue budget lines of the project.{br}

{{Total Released Retainage}} is the sum of amounts of the released AR retainage documents that are related to the project.{br}

Once the contract cap is reached, in the subsequent invoices, the system reallocates the accumulated retainage amount on each billing line based on a line weight calculation. For each pro forma invoice line, {{Line Weight}} is calculated as follows:{br}

{{Line Weight = (Amount to Invoice + Previously Invoiced) / Total Completed}}{br}

where {{Total Completed}} is the sum of {{Amount to Invoice}} and {{Previously Invoiced}} amounts for all pro forma invoice lines.[anchor|#section_rn5_wdv_qmb]
==Retainage in AIA Reports==
The calculated '''Allocated Retained Amount''' of a pro forma invoice line is shown in the '''Retainage Held''' column in the continuation sheet of AIA report prepared on the [HelpRoot_Construction\PM_64_40_00|AIA Report] ([~/?ScreenId=PM644000|PM644000]) or [HelpRoot_Construction\PM_64_45_00|AIA Report with Quantity] ([~/?ScreenId=PM644500|PM644500]) form. In the AIA report prepared for the project with the contract cap retainage, the retainage held amount is equal to the allocated retained amount from pro forma invoice that was calculated by the formula. ((({S:Warn}In projects with other retainage modes, a pro forma invoice prepared for a project does not include the allocated retained amount. In the AIA report prepared for such project, the retainage held amount it is equal to the '''Retainage Amount''' of the pro forma invoice.
)))
The total retainage amount on the cover sheet of the AIA report is calculated as the sum of the held retainage amounts on the AIA continuation sheet. Once the retainage is released, the released retainage amount is included in the current payment due amount.

