==Printing RFI Reports==
To prepare a printable form of a request for information, you use the ''RFI Question and Answer Form (PJ661000)'' form. You can open this by clicking the '''Print RFI''' button on the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_30_10_00|Request for Information] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ301000|PJ301000]) form when a particular request for information is open on the form.

A drawing log is a collection of drawings and designs related to a project. A member of a project team can create a drawing log, specify all relevant settings of the drawing log, and upload a drawing or a group of drawings to the drawing log. ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#_2c236344-6f35-4c0f-8d98-480e106f960d] *Configure drawing logs and set up disciplines and statuses *Create drawing logs *Upload and download images linked to drawing logs *Link requests for information and project issues to existing drawing logs *Email drawings and requests for information *Create revisions of drawing logs
==Applicable Scenarios== You create a drawing log when a new file with a drawing, design, or sketch needs to be associated with a project and no drawing log has already been created for the project. ==Drawing Log Creation== You can create a drawing log on one of the following forms:[anchor|#_87b34863-8e9f-4412-aa4e-91b782a746cb] *[HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_30_30_00|Drawing Log] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ303000|PJ303000]): On this entry form, you create one drawing log and specify all of its settings. *[HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_40_30_00|Drawing Logs] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ403000|PJ403000]): On this inquiry form, you can view a list of drawing logs. You can also initiate the creation of a drawing log on this form.
If any changes have been made to the initial drawing, you can update the drawing by uploading a new file version to the existing drawing log or creating a new revision of the drawing. If the uploaded drawing is an update of a previous drawing in the log, you should specify the revision number that indicates the up-to-date version of the drawing.{br}
Additionally, you can upload sketches (that is, drafts of drawings). When you upload a sketch, you should specify the sketch number in the '''Sketch''' box. ==Related RFI and Project Issues== To link a drawing log to a request for information (RFI), you can click '''Create''' > '''New RFI''' on the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_30_30_00|Drawing Log] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ303000|PJ303000]) form. The system creates the RFI, whose settings you specify, and links this RFI to the drawing log. When you send an email with the RFI, you can attach drawings from the linked drawing log to the email. Also, from the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_40_30_00|Drawing Logs] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ403000|PJ403000]) form, you can create an RFI that is linked to multiple drawing logs.{br}
From the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_30_30_00|Drawing Log] form, you can create a project issue linked to a particular drawing log. To do so, you click '''Create''' > '''New Project Issues'''. The system creates the project issue, whose settings you specify, and links this project issue to the drawing log. When you send an email with the project issue, you can attach drawings from the linked drawing log to the email. Also, from the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_40_30_00|Drawing Logs] form, you can create a project issue that is linked to multiple drawing logs.

