The following activity will walk you through the process of reconciliation of a bank statement.[anchor|#_64a986a9-ca35-41dc-82df-033738bd87f3]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. ))) ==Story== Suppose that engineers of the SweetLife company used a corporate card related to the New York Bank. At the end of January, 2020, the New York Bank sent a monthly statement and an accountant of the company reconciled this statement and processed a bill for the bank in the system. ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this lesson, the standard set of features has been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GL_20_25_00|Chart of Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=GL202500|GL202500]) form, the ''29000 - Corporate Credit Card'' account has been created. On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CA_20_20_00|Cash Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CA202000|CA202000]) form, the ''29000'' cash account linked to the GL account has been created.{br}
