In your company’s AP bills, a sales tax is a tax paid by the company to its vendors as a part of an AP bill amount; in Acumatica ERP, the system calculates the sales tax in vendor documents automatically.{br}
The system calculates taxes based on the following details specified in the document:[anchor|#ul_xfy_1mg_lq] *The vendor *The inventory IDs *The total price of the inventory items *The document date {br}
The system calculates the tax and taxable amounts by using the settings of each tax that corresponds to both the tax category of the specified inventory ID and the tax zone of the selected vendor. The system calculates the tax and taxable amounts for each line of the document or for the total document amount, depending on the settings of the applied tax (for details, see ). The system inserts the sales tax amount in the '''Tax Total''' box in the Summary area of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form.{br}
After you have released the document, the system creates the corresponding GL transaction and records these amounts to the appropriate GL accounts.{br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== From reading the topics in this chapter and completing the process activity, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#_67c458f5-6e7f-401c-86c2-b35ca64b6f03] *Learn how to configure a sales tax *Learn how to create an AP bill with a sales tax applied *Release the AP bill and review the GL batch generated by the system
==Applicable Scenarios== You create an AP bill with at least one sales tax to record a purchase subject to sales taxes.

