The length of the identifier, which can consist of only alphanumeric characters and spaces, can be up to 10 characters. |- | '''Status''' | The status of the cost projection revision, which can be one of the following: [anchor|#ul_htm_51z_w1b] *''On Hold'': The user can edit the cost projection revision but cannot release it. *''Pending Approval'': The cost projection revision has been taken off hold (that is, the status was assigned when the '''Hold''' check box was cleared for the cost projection revision). *:This status is available only if the ''Approval Workflow'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form and cost projection revision approval is configured on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_10_10_00|Projects Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PM101000|PM101000]) form. *''Rejected'': The system assigns this status to the cost projection revision if the employee who was assigned to approve the cost projection revision has rejected it. *:This status is available only if the ''Approval Workflow'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form and cost projection approval is configured on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_10_10_00|Projects Preferences] form. *''Open'': The system assigns this status to the cost projection revision if the employee who was assigned to approve the cost projection revision has approved it. If no approval is configured for cost projections, the system assigns this status to the cost projection revision when the '''Hold''' check box is cleared. *''Released'': The cost projection revision has been released and cannot be edited.
|- | '''Hold''' | A check box that you select to indicate that the cost projection should have the ''On Hold'' status. When you clear the check box, the system gives the cost projection the ''Open'' status thus indicating that the cost projection is ready to processing, or the ''Pending Approval'' status if cost projection approval is configured on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_10_10_00|Projects Preferences] form. |- | '''Description''' | The description of the cost projection. |- | '''Class''' | The cost projection class of the cost projection revision which is defined on the [HelpRoot_Construction\PM_20_35_00|Cost Projection Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=PM203500|PM203500]) form and defines the detail level of the cost projection. |- | '''Revision Date''' | The date of creating a cost projection revision. |- | colspan="2" | '''Budgeted''' section |- | '''Total Cost to Complete''' | The remainder of the budgeted cost by all cost budget lines added on the '''Details''' tab calculated as the sum of the '''Cost to Complete''' amounts. |- | '''Total Cost at Completion''' | The budgeted final cost at the moment of project completion by all cost budget added on the '''Details''' tab calculated as the sum of the '''Cost at Completion''' amounts. |- | colspan="2" | '''Projected''' section |- | '''Total Cost to Complete''' | The projected remainder of the budgeted cost by all cost budget lines added on the '''Details''' tab calculated as the sum of the '''Projected Cost to Complete''' amounts. |- | '''Total Cost at Completion''' | The projected final cost at the moment of project completion by all cost budget added on the '''Details''' tab calculated as the sum of the '''Projected Cost at Completion''' amounts. |}[anchor|#3] ==Details Tab== On this tab, you can add the cost budget lines of the project to the cost projection revision.[anchor|#table_psv_rsd_sh] ===Table Toolbar===[anchor|#_957a549e-fa1e-454a-a201-89796c4bc048] The table toolbar includes standard buttons and buttons