evision. |}[anchor|#4] ===History Window===The table toolbar in the window includes only standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Details_Table|Tables]. {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Column !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Revision''' | The identifier of the cost projection revision. |- | '''Revision Date''' | The date of the cost projection revision. |- | '''Budgeted Quantity''' | The budgeted quantity of the cost budget line in the revision of cost projection. |- | '''Budgeted Cost''' | The budgeted cost of the cost budget line in the revision of cost projection. |- | '''Actual + Committed Open Quantity''' | The sum of the actual quantity and committed open quantity of the cost budget line in the revision of cost projection. |- | '''Actual + Committed Open Cost''' | The sum of the actual cost and committed open cost of the cost budget line in the revision of cost projection. |- | '''Quantity to Complete''' | The remainder of the budgeted quantity of the cost budget line that is currently available for completion in the revision of cost projection. This quantity is calculated by the following formula: {{Quantity to Complete = Budgeted Quantity – (Actual Quantity + Revised Committed Quantity – Invoiced Committed Quantity)}} |- | '''Cost to Complete''' | The remainder of the budgeted cost of the cost budget line that is currently available for completion in the revision of cost projection. This cost is calculated by the following formula: {{Cost to Complete = Budgeted Cost – (Actual Cost + Revised Committed Cost – Invoiced Committed Cost)}} |- | '''Projected Quantity to Complete''' | The projected remainder of the budgeted quantity for the cost budget line in the revision of cost projection, which by default is equal to the '''Quantity to Complete'''. |- | '''Projected Cost to Complete''' | The projected remainder of the budgeted cost for the cost budget line in the revision of cost projection, which by default is equal to the '''Cost to Complete'''. |}[anchor|#table_adz_3fh_smb] ===Table Columns=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Column !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Account Group''' | The expense account group of the cost budget line. |- | '''Cost Task''' | The project task to which the cost budget line relates. |- | '''Inventory ID''' | The stock or non-stock inventory item that is associated with the cost budget line. |- | '''Description''' | The description entered for the cost budget line. |- | '''UOM''' | The unit of measure of the cost budget line. |- | '''Budgeted Quantity''' | The budgeted quantity of the cost budget line specified in the project. |- | '''Budgeted Cost''' | The budgeted cost of the cost budget line specified in the project. |- | '''Actual + Committed Open Quantity''' | The sum of the actual quantity and committed open quantity of the cost budget line specified in the project. |- | '''Actual + Committed Open Cost''' | The sum of the actual cost and committed open cost of the cost budget line specified in the project.. |- | '''Quantity to Complete''' | The remainder of the budgeted quantity of the cost budget line that is currently available for completion. This quantity is calculated by the following formula: {{Quantity to Complete = Budgeted Quantity – (Actual Quantity + Revised Committed Quantity – Invoiced Committed Quantity)}} |- | '''Cost to Complete''' | The remainder of the budgeted cost of the cost budget line that is currently available for completion. This cost is calculated by the following formula: {{Cost to Complete = Budgeted Cost – (Actual Cost + Revised Committed Cost – Invoiced Committed Cost)}} |- | '''Projected Quantity to Complete''' | The projected remainder of the budgeted quantity for the cost budget line, which by default is equal to the '''Quantity to Complete'''; the system recalculates this quantity if you change any other projected value in the line and the recalculation mode in the '''Mode''' box in the line is set to ''Auto'' or ''Manual Cost''. If you override this value, the corresponding values in the cost budget line will be recalculated based on the recalculation mode of the line. |- | '''Projected Cost to Complete''' | The projected remainder of the budgeted cost for the cost budget line, which by default is equal to the '''Cost to Complete'''; the system recalculates this cost if you change any other projected value in the line and the recalculation mode in the line is set to ''Auto'' or ''Manual Quantity''. If you override this value, the corresponding values in the cost budget line will be recalculated based on the recalculation mode of the line. |- | '''Projected Quantity at Completion''' | The projected final quantity at the moment of project completion for the cost budget line. By default, this quantity is calculated by the following formula: {{Projected Quantity at Completion = Projected Quantity to Complete + Actual Quantity + Revised Committed Quantity – Invoiced Committed Quantity}} If you override this value, the corresponding values in the cost budget line will be recalculated based on the recalculation mode of the line. |- | '''Projected Cost at Completion''' | The projected final cost at the moment of project completion for the cost budget line. By default, this cost is calculated by the following formula: {{Projected Cost at Completion = Projected Cost to Complete + Actual Cost + Revised Committed Cost – Invoiced Committed Cost}} If you override this value, the corresponding values in the cost budget line will be recalculated based on the recalculation mode of the line. |- | '''Projected Completed (%)''' | The projected percentage of completion for the cost budget line. By default, this percentage is calculated by the following formula: {{Projected Completed (%) = (Budgeted Cost – Projected Cost to Complete) / Budgeted Cost * 100%}} If you override this value, the corresponding values in the cost budget line will be recalculated based on the recalculation mode of the line. |- | '''Mode''' | The mode that specifies how the amounts and quantities are recalculated for the cost budget line. The following options are available:[anchor|#ul_u2c_hs4_smb] *''Auto'': If specified, the system automatically recalculates projected quantities and costs if any other projected value in the cost budget line is being changed. *''Manual'': If specified, the system do not recalculate projected quantities and costs if any other projected value in the cost budget line is being changed. *''Manual Quantity'': If specified, the system automatically recalculates projected costs if any other projected value in the cost budget line is being changed; the '''Projected Quantity to Complete''' and '''Projected Quantity at Completion''' values are preserved. *''Manual Cost'': If specified, the system automatically recalculates projected quantities if any other projected value in the cost budget line is being changed; the '''Projected Cost to Complete''' and '''Projected Cost at Completion''' values are preserved.
