Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=CL301000|CL301000]){br}
With this form, you can create, view, and modify compliance attributes. You can enter the needed custom attributes for each compliance document type and define your custom statuses for compliance documents. Also you can add and update common attributes for all types of compliance documents. Custom attributes can be assigned only to compliance documents. Each organization could have their proper attributes for compliance documents. {br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar== The form toolbar includes standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. ==Custom Attributes Tab== On this tab, you can specify custom attributes for each type of the compliance document.[anchor|#_205bbbb6-3a84-4353-b26d-5152673d337e] ===Table Toolbar===The table toolbar includes standard buttons and buttons specific to this table. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Details_Toolbar|Table Toolbar]. The table-specific buttons are listed below. {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Button !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Attribute''' | The menu containing the list of predefined attributes for compliance documents. The following attributes are allowed:[anchor|#_126c31d7-494e-4e0b-bbb1-7299cfd3c01e] *''Certificate'': The type of the compliance document. *''Insurance'': The type of the compliance document. *''Lien Waiver'': The type of the compliance document. *''Notice'': The type of the compliance document. *''Status'': The status of the compliance document.
