Form ID: (PMGI0030){br}
You use this form to view the revisions of the selected pro forma invoice, including the current revision and the previous ones if the pro forma invoice has been corrected.{br}
This form is available if the ''Construction'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}{TOC} ==Table Toolbar==[anchor|#_5ae8a0f1-ba13-4af8-bc15-66dc03554b50] The table toolbar includes only standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Details_Toolbar|Table Toolbar].[anchor|#1] ==Selection Area== You use the elements in this area to select a pro forma invoice whose revisions you want the system display in the table.[anchor|#_36cbf624-e3ce-40c8-a50d-e3c0fade0644] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Reference Nbr.''' | The identifier of the pro forma invoice whose revisions you want to view. |} ==Table== In the table, you can review lines of all the revisions of the pro forma invoice that is selected in the Selection area. The lines are sorted ascending by the invoice line number and then descending by the invoice revision—that is, the system shows all the revisions of the first invoice line, then all the revisions of the second line, and so on. The lines of the current revision are highlighted with green and have the highest revision number.[anchor|#_dddc1cbe-acb3-47b7-b25e-1f5075c15216]{br}
The table toolbar includes only standard buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Details_Toolbar|Table Toolbar].[anchor|#_ca1d372a-7fb5-497e-949b-48ee07572f5b] ===Table Columns=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Column !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Sort Order''' | The number of the invoice line in the invoice revision. |- | '''Revision''' | The revision number of the pro forma invoice, which is an integer that the system assigns sequentially, starting from 1. |- | '''Project ID''' | The project associated with the invoice line. |- | '''Project Task''' | The project task with which the invoice line is associated. |- | '''Account Group''' | The account group associated with the invoice line. |- | '''Cost Code''' | The cost code associated with the invoice line.{br}
The column is available if the ''Cost Code'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. |- | '''Inventory ID''' | The inventory item associated with the invoice line. |- | '''Description''' | The description of the invoice line. |- | '''Amount''' | The original line amount calculated by the billing rule. |- | '''Stored Material''' | The amount of material stored. |- | '''Amount to Invoice''' | The amount to bill the customer. |- | '''Retainage (%)''' | The percent of the invoice line amount to be retained by the customer.{br}
The column appears in the table if the ''Retainage Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. |- | '''Retainage Amount''' | The amount to be retained by the customer.{br}
The column appears in the table if the ''Retainage Support'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. |- | '''Tax Category''' | The tax category of the invoice line. |}

Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=PJ302000|PJ302000])[anchor|#note_oxf_l5c_5z]((({S:Warn}This form is available only if the ''Construction'' and ''Construction Project Management'' features are enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. ))) You can use this form to create, view, and edit each project issue that has been discovered during construction. On this form, you track and report all activities related to the selected project issue. If needed, you can create a request for information or change request based on the selected issue.{br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_f7d188d8-2336-46aa-802c-713bf45df0d1] The form toolbar includes standard and form-specific buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. The form-specific buttons are listed below.[anchor|#_e8293a69-7ecc-4c8b-9076-8aff7e0494c7] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Button !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Convert to RFI''' | Creates a request for information for the project issue, and opens the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_30_10_00|Request for Information] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ301000|PJ301000]) form with the created request for information. |- | '''Convert to Change Request''' | Creates a change request for the project issue, and opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_85_00|Change Requests] ([~/?ScreenId=PM308500|PM308500]) form with the created change request. |- | '''Print/Email''' | Opens the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_66_20_00|Project Issue Form] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ662000|PJ662000]), which displays a print-friendly version of the project issue that can be printed or sent by email. |}[anchor|#1] ==Summary Area== Here you can create a new project issue or select an existing project issue for modification. The following table summarizes the elements of this area. [anchor|#_5b36108b-e9c1-483d-80a8-21fa680546ba] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Element !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Summary''' | A brief description of the issue that happened. |- | '''Project Issue ID''' | The reference number of the project issue, which the system automatically assigns according to the numbering sequence selected for project issues on the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_10_10_00|Project Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ101000|PJ101000]) form. |- | '''Project''' | The project related to the issue. |- | '''Project Task''' | The project task related to the issue. |- | '''Class ID''' | The project management class that the project issue belongs to. For a new project issue, you select a class, which populates some elements with default values, easing data entry. |- | '''Related Entity''' | The entity related to the project issue. You assign the entity by clicking the magnifier icon in this box and specifying the necessary entity settings in the '''Select Entity''' dialog box. |- | '''Converted To''' | The reference number of the request for information or change request created for the project issue. The system fills in this box when the request for information or change request is saved. You can click the link to open the document on the related form. |- | '''Due Date''' | The date on which the project issue has to be resolved. |- | '''Priority''' | The priority of the project issue. The following options are available: ''Low'', ''Medium'', and ''High''. The default priority is specified for the class of the project issue on the '''Priorities''' tab of the [HelpRoot_Construction\PJ_20_10_00|Project Management Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=PJ201000|PJ201000]) form. |- | '''Status''' | The status of the project issue, which is ''Open'' or ''Closed''. |- | '''Created On''' | The date and time when the project issue has been created. By default, the system inserts the current business date. |- | '''Created By''' | The user name of the employee that has created the project issue. By default, the currently assigned user is selected. |- | '''Owner''' | The user name of the employee assigned to the project issue. If a workgroup has been selected, a user name can be selected only from its list of group members; otherwise, the user name may be selected from the list of all users. |- | '''Workgroup''' | The workgroup to work on the project issue. |- | '''Resolved On''' | The date when the issue has been resolved. |- | '''Project Issue Type''' | The type of the project issue. |- | '''Schedule Impact''' | A check box that indicates (if selected) that this project issue has caused the project schedule to change. |- | '''Schedule Impact (days)''' | The number of days by which the project schedule has been delayed by the project issue.{br}
This box appears on the form only if the '''Schedule Impact''' check box is selected. |- | '''Cost Impact''' | A check box that indicates (if selected) that the cost of the project has been affected by the project issue. |- | '''Cost Impact''' | The amount by which the project budget has been increased as a result of the project issue. {br}
This box appears on the form only if the '''Cost Impact''' check box is selected. |} ==Details Tab== This tab contains an area you can use to describe the project issue. The area consists of the following:[anchor|#_bc822661-079b-4457-82fe-05ff01dc6ac9] *The formatting toolbar, with buttons you can use to edit the text, change its typographical treatment, and format it. You can also use buttons to add files and insert images. *The '''Message''' text box, where you can enter a detailed description of the project issue or relevant notes. You can type the description here and edit its text by using the buttons on the formatting toolbar. [anchor|#2] ==Related Activities== This tab has a table with the list of activities associated with the project issue. You can associate particular emails and activities with the project issue. {br}
