Form ID: ([~/?ScreenId=SC301000|SC301000]){br}
On this form, you can view existing subcontracts, create new subcontracts, and add lines to subcontracts. Once a subcontract has been saved, it can be approved, rejected, or canceled by any employee assigned to review this subcontract.{br}{TOC} ==Form Toolbar==[anchor|#_07384ac8-47ab-40e5-9999-7ce9f32fa6d2] The form toolbar includes standard and form-specific buttons. For the list of standard buttons, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Form_Toolbar|Form Toolbar]. The form-specific buttons are listed below.[anchor|#_770fc7f2-7392-46c2-ab6f-8b0111afe5c3] {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="20%" ! Button !width="80%" ! Description |- | '''Actions''' | Provides the following menu commands, which you can click to invoke actions:[anchor|#_8194715d-09f9-4c5b-b431-a663971e52af] *'''Approve''': Approves the current subcontract. *:This action is available if the ''Approval Workflow'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. *'''Reject''': Rejects the current subcontract. After a subcontract has been rejected, you can change its status to ''On Hold'', correct the subcontract, take it off hold, and save your changes, which subjects the subcontract to approval again. *:This action is available if the ''Approval Workflow'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *'''Email Subcontract''': Emails (based on the settings of the ''SUBCONTRACT'' mailing) the subcontract to the vendor specified in this subcontract. *:For more information, see [HelpRoot_Financials\AR__con_Predefined_Mailings_for_Customers_and_Vendors|Mailings for Customers]. *'''Mark as Do Not Email''': Causes the '''Don’t Email''' check box (on the '''Other Information''' tab) to be selected for the subcontract, to skip the step of emailing the subcontract. *'''Enter AP Bill''': Creates an accounts payable bill based on the current subcontract. This action opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form with a new accounts payable bill that has all the details copied from the subcontract. *'''Complete Subcontract''': Completes the current subcontract, which changes its status to ''Closed''. *'''Cancel Subcontract''': Cancels the subcontract, which changes its status to ''Canceled''. A subcontract with this status cannot be edited. You can later manually change its status to ''On Hold'' (by selecting the '''Hold''' check box) and edit the subcontract. *'''Validate Addresses''': Validates the account addresses through integration with a specialized third-party software or service. *:This action appears only if the ''Address Validation'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. *'''Recalculate Prices''': Opens the [[#_6e0cb5d7-179c-4c12-997d-6341da69c689|Recalculate Prices] dialog box, which you can use to specify the extent to which you want to refresh the prices and discounts for the document. *'''Create Prepayment Request''': Creates a prepayment linked to this subcontract. The system opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form with a new prepayment request (based on the subcontract) that is ready to be saved. The prepayment can be used to pay for this subcontract directly when the goods are received.
|- | '''Reports''' | Provides the following menu command, which you can click for quick navigation to the form:[anchor|#_77392c9e-c056-4e16-b78f-7830928ec833] *'''Vendor Details''': Opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_40_20_00|Vendor Details] ([~/?ScreenId=AP402000|AP402000]) form, which displays the data related to the vendor from which the goods in this subcontract are ordered. *'''Print Subcontract''': Opens the [HelpRoot_Construction\SC_64_10_00|Subcontract] ([~/?ScreenId=SC641000|SC641000]) report form that you can use to print the current subcontract.
